Invalidate cache: aws cloudfront create-invalidation --distribution-id D12345 --paths "/index.html"
Test SSL cert: openssl s_client -connect dxxxx.cloudfront.net:443
Lessons Learned
CloudFront caches content globally; invalidation is needed after updates.

Targeted invalidation saves cost/time compared to invalidating all files.

SSL/TLS issues often come from missing or expired ACM certificates.

Monitoring CloudFront logs helps confirm cache hits/misses.

